article.description: Ladarius Knight had 11 points off the bench to carry Campbell to a 62-57 win over Jacksonville on Monday night.
article.headline: Knight, bench play boosts Campbell past Jacksonville 62-57
article.linkText: Knight, bench play boosts Campbell past Jacksonville 62-57
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- Ladarius Knight had 11 points off the bench to carry Campbell to a 62-57 win over Jacksonville on Monday night. Ja'Cor Nelson had 10 points and six rebounds for Campbell (4-1). Jesus Carralero added five assists. David Bell had 14 points and 11 rebounds for the Dolphins (3-5). Bryce Workman added seven rebounds. Campbell faces Georgia Southern on Friday. Jacksonville takes on NC A&T on the road on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
